This is one of those articles that makes me envious that I can't write this sort of thing myself. It's wonderfully bizarre, but still manages to be terrifying, coherent, and intriguing at the same time, all while maintaining that sense of grand space-ness that shows up in a lot of your stuff. It's genuinely astounding that you can still write scips like this without retreading the same old ground.

Solid upvote :)







